LYDENBERG - A taxi crash in Mpumalanga s Lydenburg left 18 people injured on Wednesday afternoon, with two of them reportedly in critical condition.The taxi reportedly drove into a tractor under a railway bridge on Voortrekker Street shortly before 5 o clock.READ: 23 injured in Durban minibus taxi crashThe injured were transported to a nearby hospital, and the cause of the crash is being investigated. eNCA